message:
P4 here. We’re five seats, two clear pairs (P1-P5, P4-P8) and one free agent (P2). If we hammer the solo now we guarantee a 2-2 gridlock at four—hello coin-flip finale. Smarter play: form a transparent triangle this round, then fight it out at three where every vote counts. I’ll commit to:

1) mutual no-hit with any two who join;  
2) target locked 30 min pre-vote;  
3) zero last-second pivots.

P2, you’d hold swing power—interested?
